coration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;"">, but the band gradually ventured into more conventional and radio-friendly works by incorporating further styles, such as&nbsp;</span><a href=""https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arena_rock"" title=""Arena rock"" style=""text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); border-radius: 2px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal;"">arena rock</a><span style=""color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;"">&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><a href=""https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pop_rock"" title=""Pop rock"" style=""text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); border-radius: 2px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal;"">pop rock</a><span style=""color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;"">.</span></p><p><span style=""color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;""><img src=""https://res.cloudinary.com/dc1pocu3o/image/upload/v1762616242/queen-1.jpg"" style=""width: 300px;"" class=""fr-fic fr-dib""></span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=""color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;"" data-pasted=""true"">Before forming Queen, May and Taylor had played together in the band&nbsp;</span><a href=""https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smile_(band)"" title=""Smile (band)"" style=""text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); border-radius: 2px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal;"">Smile</a><span style=""color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;"">. Mercury was a fan of Smile and encouraged them to experiment with more elaborate stage and recording techniques. He joined in 1970 and suggested the name &quot;Queen&quot;. Deacon was recruited in February 1971, before the band released their&nbsp;</span><a href=""https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Queen_(Queen_album)"" title=""Queen (Queen album)"" style=""text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); border-radius: 2px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal;"">self-titled debut album</a><span style=""color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;"">&nbsp;in 1973. Queen first charted in the UK with their second album,&nbsp;</span><i style=""color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;""><a href=""https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Queen_II"" title=""Queen II"" style=""text-decoration: none; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background: none; border-radius: 2px; overflow-wrap: break-word;"">Queen II</a></i><span style=""color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;"">, in 1974.&nbsp;</span><i style=""color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decorat