                            Content = @"
                            <p data-start=""190"" data-end=""551"" data-pasted=""true"">Kurt Cobain was an American musician best known as the lead singer, guitarist, and songwriter of <strong data-start=""287"" data-end=""298"">Nirvana</strong>, one of the most influential rock bands of the early 1990s. Born on <strong data-start=""367"" data-end=""388"">February 20, 1967</strong>, in <strong data-start=""393"" data-end=""417"">Aberdeen, Washington</strong>, Cobain showed an early passion for art and music but also struggled with feelings of isolation and instability during his childhood.</p><p data-start=""190"" data-end=""551""><br></p><p data-start=""553"" data-end=""870"">In 1987, he formed Nirvana with bassist <strong data-start=""593"" data-end=""612"">Krist Novoselic</strong>. The band&rsquo;s breakthrough came with the 1991 album <strong data-start=""663"" data-end=""678""><em data-start=""665"" data-end=""676"">Nevermind</em></strong>, which included the iconic anthem &ldquo;<strong data-start=""714"" data-end=""741"">Smells Like Teen Spirit</strong>.&rdquo; The song catapulted Nirvana&mdash;and the grunge movement&mdash;into global fame, turning Cobain into a reluctant voice of his generation.</p><p data-start=""553"" data-end=""870""><br></p><p data-start=""872"" data-end=""1193"">Despite success, Cobain battled <strong data-start=""904"" data-end=""952"">depression, chronic pain, and drug addiction</strong>, all of which deeply influenced his lyrics and worldview. His marriage to musician <strong data-start=""1036"" data-end=""1053"">Courtney Love</strong> in 1992 and the birth of their daughter <strong data-start=""1094"" data-end=""1117"">Frances Bean Cobain</strong> brought moments of happiness, but fame and pressure weighed heavily on him.</p><p data-start=""872"" data-end=""1193""><br></p><p data-start=""1195"" data-end=""1436"">Tragically, Kurt Cobain <strong data-start=""1219"" data-end=""1255"">died by suicide on April 5, 1994</strong>, at the age of 27, joining the so-called &ldquo;27 Club.&rdquo; His legacy continues through his music, which remains raw, emotional, and timeless&mdash;a reflection of both his pain and his genius.</p>
